<p>To season the fish, she rubbed the salmon with lime-infused olive oil, parsley, thyme and dill, which made the food taste 'so delicious'.</p>

<p>Diane originally found a simple recipe in a cookbook but opted to use the handy air fryer rather than the oven. </p>

<p>On Facebook other home cooks agreed and said the air fryer is the best gadget for cooking fish and other types of meat. </p>

<p>'Was a sceptic about how well the air fryer would cook salmon. It was perfect,' she said online and shared images to a popular Australian Facebook group </p>

<p>'It cooks salmon to perfection. Yours look delicious,' one person said.</p>

<p>'Salmon is the absolute best in the air fryer,' another added.</p>

<p>'Am doing pork tonight, did barramundi last night. So moist,' a third said.</p>

<p>The online post was 'liked' more than 230 times and 111 others commented by tagging friends to share the recipe further. </p>

<p>Earlier in September, another home cook revealed how she made prawn toast  (pictured) in her $89 5.3 litre Kmart air fryer after a similar recipe was shared on MasterChef Australia</p>

<p>Earlier in September, another home cook revealed how she made prawn toast in her $89 5.3 litre Kmart air fryer after a similar recipe was shared on MasterChef Australia. </p>

<p>Lynette, from Melbourne, posted the recipe to a popular cookery group where others raved about how delicious it was. </p>

<p>'Recipe is a modified version from Sarah Tiong Masterchef Au 2020, recipe makes 12 slices,' she said online.</p>

<p>Prawn toast is a Chinese dish made from bread brushed with egg or oil and coated with minced prawn. </p>

<p>To make the toast, she used bread slices, prawns, sesame oil, fresh ginger, sesame seeds, garlic and salt and pepper to season.</p>

<p>The recipe itself is simple to follow and only takes less than 15 minutes to complete from start to finish.</p>
